Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the oven to 450 degrees. Thinly slice the
@sweet potato{12%ounce} into 1/8-inch rounds, like chips. Toss the rounds on a
#baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp}, then season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}. Bake in the oven for ~{25-30%minutes}, flipping halfway through
cooking, until golden brown.

Halve, peel, and mince the @shallot{1}. Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}.
Peel, then mince or grate the @ginger{1%thumb}. Finely chop the
@cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

In a #large bowl{}, combine the @ground turkey{8%ounce}, shallot, half the
ginger, half the garlic, half the cilantro, @sriracha{1/2%teaspoon}, and
@soy sauce{2%teaspoons}. Season with salt and pepper. Form the mixture into 2
patties. In a #small bowl{}, combine the @mayonnaise{1} and as much
@sriracha{2%teaspoon} as you like. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large oven-proof pan{} over medium high-heat.
Season the burgers liberally with salt and pepper. Add the burgers to the pan
and cook for ~{2-3%minutes} per side, until browned. Transfer the burgers to
the oven to finish cooking for ~{5-7%minutes}. Split the @potato buns{2} and
place in the oven to toast for ~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: If you don't have an oven-proof pan, place the burgers onto the baking
> sheet with the sweet potatoes.

== Mixed Green Salad ==

Make the mixed green salad: In a large bowl, combine the remaining ginger,
garlic, and a drizzle of oil. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Toss the
@mixed greens{2%ounce} into the bowl to coat.

== Assembly ==

Assemble the burgers: Spread a little sriracha mayo onto each bun, then top
with a sriracha turkey burger and the remaining cilantro. Serve the mixed
green salad, sweet potato crisps, and remaining sriracha mayo to the side
(for dipping!)

> TIP: You can also add some of the salad on the burger, if you like. Enjoy!